20is%20that%20the%20colors%20aren't%20always%20true.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fastronaut-photo-aurora-from-international-space-station-2021-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecolor%20of%20an%20aurora%3C%2Fa%3E%20indicates%20its%20altitude%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20type%20of%20molecules%20in%20the%20atmosphere%20that%20are%20creating%20it.%20Green%2C%20for%20example%2C%20usually%20comes%20from%20oxygen%20atoms%20at%20lower%20altitudes%20in%20the%20atmosphere.%20Pink%20or%20red%20can%20indicate%20high-altitude%20oxygen%20or%20nitrogen%20at%20very%20low%20altitudes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20phone%20also%20picked%20up%20a%20field%20of%20purple%20in%20some%20images%2C%20which%20could%20indicate%20low-altitude%20nitrogen%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0but%20that%20could%20have%20been%20a%20trick%20of%20the%20pixels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22purple%20starry%20sky%20above%20treetops%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664290319686a6f37bff8928%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESome%20of%20my%20pictures%20turned%20out%20purple%20for%20some%20reason.%3Cp%3EMorgan%20McFall-Johnsen%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BObviously%2C%20screens%20do%20not%20always%20reproduce%20the%20natural%20colours%20reliably%2C%26quot%3B%20Maria%20Walach%2C%20a%20space%20plasma%20physicist%20who%20researches%20auroras%20at%20Lancaster%20University%2C%20told%20BI%20in%20an%20email.%20%26quot%3BAdditionally%2C%20you%20can%20get%20all%20sorts%20of%20colours%20from%20mixing%20and%20different%20viewing%20angles%2C%20which%20sometimes%20makes%20it%20tricky%20to%20tell.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20of%20course%2C%20photos%20you%20see%20online%20could%20always%20be%20edited%20after%20the%20fact.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDon't%20be%20misled.%20I%20mean%2C%20the%20camera%20does%20its%20own%20processing%20but%20you%20know%20that%20you%20could%20go%20in%20and%20change%20that%20processing%20level%20to%20your%20tastes%2C%26quot%3B%20Bartlett%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20could%20saturate%20the%20colors%20and%20make%20it%20grotesque%2C%20you%20could%20do%20anything%20you%20want%20with%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222b1a3fbe-67c1-4e90-a893-43e76e0c07e3%5C%22%3EGo%20see%20the%20aurora%2C%20just%20know%20it%20might%20be%20faint%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20rare%20event%20isn't%20over.%20More%20eruptions%20on%20the%20sun%20are%20sending%20electromagnetic%20material%20our%20way%2C%20meaning%20much%20of%20the%20northern%20US%20could%20get%20the%20aurora%20again%20on%20Monday%20night.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20may%20be%20even%20more%20opportunities%20this%20year.%20After%20all%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsun-more-active-solar-storms-auroras-power-outages-grounded-flights-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20sun%20is%20close%20to%20the%20maximum%20activity%20level%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20reaches%20every%2011%20years%2C%20meaning%20there%20will%20probably%20be%20more%20solar%20eruptions%20that%20bring%20the%20aurora%20to%20unusual%20latitudes.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20it's%20absolutely%20worth%20seeing%2C%20even%20if%20it's%20faint%20like%20mine%20was.%20I'm%20glad%20I%20stayed%20out%20until%203%20a.m.%20to%20catch%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20you're%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20US%20or%20at%20a%20similar%20latitude%20elsewhere%20on%20Earth%2C%20don't%20expect%20to%20see%20the%20bright%20pink%20and%20green%20glow%20that%20photos%20all%20over%20social%20media%20are%20showing.%20They%20can%20be%20a%20bit%20misleading.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsaw-northern-lights-surprising-photos-misleading-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715641053000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com