peeds.%3Cp%3ENASA's%20Goddard%20Space%20Flight%20Center%2FJ.%20Schnittman%20and%20B.%20Powell%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20you've%20passed%20the%20photon%20ring%2C%20you're%20only%2010%20minutes%20away%20from%20reaching%20the%20event%20horizon%2C%20according%20to%20NASA's%20calculations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20those%2010%20minutes%2C%20you%20continue%20to%20see%20the%20light%20from%20the%20accretion%20disk%20and%20photon%20ring%20warp%20in%20a%20repeated%20cycle%20of%20growing%20and%20shrinking%20distorted%20ovals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20countdown%20reaches%20zero%2C%20%26quot%3Bonce%20the%20camera%20crosses%20the%20horizon%2C%20its%20destruction%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fastronomers-capture-a-black-hole-shredding-star-into-spaghetti-strands-2020-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espaghettification%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20just%2012.8%20seconds%20away%2C%26quot%3B%20Schnittman%20said%20in%20the%20NASA%20press%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpaghettification%20is%20the%20term%20to%20describe%20how%20the%20black%20hole's%20gravity%20would%20stretch%20your%20body%20to%20as%20thin%20as%20a%20piece%20of%20spaghetti%2C%20killing%20you%20in%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20point%20of%20no%20return%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222880%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22thin%20ring%20of%20red%20light%20around%20a%20black%20hole%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663e5bdff27898f532d66796%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EYour%20spaceship%20has%20passed%20the%20event%20horizon%20and%20is%20now%20trapped%20inside%20the%20black%20hole%20forever.%20Death%20is%20imminent.%20%3Cp%3ENASA's%20Goddard%20Space%20Flight%20Center%2FJ.%20Schnittman%20and%20B.%20Powell%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20this%20point%2C%20you'd%20probably%20be%20too%20worried%20about%20your%20body%20spaghettifying%20to%20look%20outside.%20But%20if%20you%20did%2C%20you'd%20see%20only%20a%20faint%2C%20thin%20red%20line%20of%20light%20as%20you%20plummeted%20toward%20the%20black%20hole's%20center.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20you%20pass%20the%20event%20horizon%2C%20it's%20only%2079%2C500%20miles%20to%20the%20very%20center%20of%20this%20black%20hole.%20A%20black%20hole's%20center%20is%20what's%20called%20the%20singularity.%20It's%20a%20mysterious%20place%20where%20gravity%20is%20so%20extreme%20that%20our%20laws%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffuture-circular-collider-push-boundaries-modern-physics-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ephysics%20break%20down%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20we%20don't%20know%20what%20happens.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20do%20know%2C%20however%2C%20that%20you'd%20be%20dead%20before%20you%20reached%20it.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHow%20black%20holes%20spaghettify%20their%20prey%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222880%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22animation%20of%20a%20yellow%20star%20being%20sucked%20into%20a%20black%20hole%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663d278bb4abc992e8c7b761%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBlack%20holes%20have%20the%20strongest%20gravitational%20pull%20of%20any%20object%20in%20our%20universe%2C%20capable%20of%20stretching%20your%20body%20as%20thin%20as%20a%20piece%20of%20spaghetti.%20%3Cp%3EEuropean%20Southern%20Observatory%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reason%20death%20by%20black%20hole%20is%20also%20sometimes%20called%20death%20by%20spaghettification%20is%20because%20of%20the%20black%20hole's%20immense%20gravity.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBlack%20holes%20have%20the%20strongest%20gravitational%20pull%20of%20any%20object%20in%20our%20universe.%20That's%20why%20they%20can%20easily%20take%20an%20entire%20star%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fastronomers-capture-a-black-hole-shredding-star-into-spaghetti-stran