ement-plans%5C%22%3Eretirement%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0since%202019.%20And%20yet%2C%20I%20completely%20believe%20in%20planning%20ahead%20for%20retirement.%20I've%20even%20worked%20to%20help%20other%20people%20understand%20why%20investing%20is%20important.%20So%20if%20my%20lack%20of%20recent%20retirement%20account%20contributions%20sounds%20unthinkable%2C%20I'll%20explain.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20saving%20for%20retirement%20in%20my%2020s%20via%20an%20employer's%20401(k)%20plan.%20I%20was%20working%20as%20a%20writer%20and%20editor%2C%20and%20retirement%20was%20decades%20away%2C%20but%20I%20knew%20the%20magic%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-compound-interest%5C%22%3Ecompound%20interest%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20help%20set%20up%20my%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20I'd%20been%20working%20for%20offered%20matching%20funds%20with%20a%20staggered%20vesting%20schedule.%20Admittedly%2C%20it%20was%20not%20the%20best.%20But%20I%20still%20contributed%20pre-tax%2C%20not%20knowing%20if%20I'd%20ever%20get%20the%20full%20matching%20payout.%20(Spoiler%3A%20I%20didn't.)%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFast%20forward%20to%20my%20next%20job%2C%20where%20I%20continued%20to%20contribute%20to%20a%20401(k)%20with%20every%20paycheck.%20This%20employer%20had%20a%20more%20generous%20policy%2C%20with%20a%20company%20match%20of%20up%20to%205%25%20of%20funds%20and%20immediate%20vesting.%20I%20was%20getting%20free%20money%2C%20y'all%2C%20and%20it%20was%20a%20great%20motivator.%20I%20could%20see%20my%20retirement%20accounts%20growing.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'll%20spare%20you%20my%20whole%20workplace%20journey%2C%20but%20I%20eventually%20ended%20up%20at%20an%20agency%20that%20matched%20up%20to%205%25%20of%20my%20retirement%20contributions.%20There%2C%20I%20was%20vested%20fully%20after%20three%20years%2C%20and%20I%20even%20rolled%20in%20a%20previous%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-401k%5C%22%3E401(k)%3C%2Fa%3E%20plan%20to%20consolidate%20my%20investments%20with%20lower%20fees.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20this%20job%2C%20I'd%20regularly%20contribute%20the%20minimum%20required%20for%20matching%20and%2C%20at%20times%2C%20more%20than%2010%25%20of%20my%20salary.%20My%20focus%20was%20on%20saving%20money%2C%20growing%20my%20retirement%20account%2C%20and%20reducing%20taxable%20income.%20But%20when%20I%20decided%20to%20leave%20that%20staff%20job%20to%20find%20freedom%20and%20work%20for%20myself%2C%20I%20also%20left%20the%20matching%20funds%20and%20lost%20the%20ability%20to%20add%20more.%20So%2C%C2%A0I%20stopped%20investing%20in%20workplace%20retirement%20accounts.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EGoing%20freelance%20changed%20my%20perspective%20on%20retirement%20planning%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20new%20stage%2C%20I%20could%20have%20started%20contributing%20to%20after-tax%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-ira-accounts%5C%22%3EIRAs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20my%20perspective%20on%20retirement%20planning%20had%20changed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20see%2C%20when%20I%20went%20freelance%2C%20I%20decided%20I%20needed%20to%20be%20more%20financially%20liquid.%20This%20would%20help%20while%20I%20ramped%20up%20my%20business%20and%20give%20me%20a%20cushion%20in%20case%20of%20emergency.%20Because%20there's%20no%20paid%20time%20off%20for%20consultants%20%E2%80%94%20unless%20you've%20mastered%20passive%20income%2C%20but%20that's%20%3Cem%3Eanother%3C%2Fem%3E%20story%20%E2%80%94%20so%20it's%20helpful%20to%20have%20funds%20on%20hand.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20traditional%20retirement%20accounts%20can%20be%20helpful%20for%20long-term%20planning%2C%20especially%20when%20you're%20an%20employee%20receiving%20a%20vested%20company%20match%2C%20circumstances%20do%20change.%20In%20my%20case%2C%20I%20absolutely%20did%20not%20want%20to%20be%20faced%20with%20a%20penalty%20if%20I%20wanted%20to%20withdraw%20funds%20before%20retirement%20age.%20(Another%20thing%20I%20considered%3F%20While%20pre-tax%20retirement%20accounts%20can%20help%20employees%20reduce%20taxable%20income%2C%20business%20owners%20like%20me%20can%20reduce%20taxable%20income%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.irs.gov%2Fforms-pubs%2Fguide-to-business-expense-resources%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ededucting%20qualified%20business%20expenses%3C%2Fa%3E.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20my%20answer%20to%20being%20more%20liquid%20%E2%80%94%20and%20more%20in%20control%20of%20my%20finances%20%E2%80%94%20was%20%3Cem%3Enot%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20funnel%20all%20money%20into%20a%20bank%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-high-yield-savings-accounts-rates-right-now%5C%22%3Esavings%20account%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20hope%20for%20the%20best.%20Because%20inflation%20is%20real.%20And%20fiat%20money%20stowed%20in%20a%20savings%20account%20loses%20value%20over%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20days%2C%20as%20inflation%20rises%2C%20I%20now%20have%20more%20funds%20in%20investments%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-to-invest-in-index-funds%5C%22%3Eindex%20funds%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20few%20stocks%2C%20and%20cryptocurrencies.%20And%20you%20know%20what%3F%20While%20my%20retirement%20accounts%20from%20previous%20staff%20jobs%20continue%20to%20grow%2C%20and%20are%20not%20too%20shabby%2C%20my%20after-tax%20investments%20aren't%20too%20shabby%20either.%20And%20I'm%20thankful.%20Because%20while%20we%20continue%20to%20deal%20with%20economic%20uncertainty%2C%20I%20can%20move%20or%20withdraw%20my%20after-tax%20funds%20if%20I%20need%20to%20%E2%80%94%20without%20penalty.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI'm%20happy%20to%20adjust%20as%20needed%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20I%20appreciate%20the%20old%20me%20for%20investing%20via%20employer%20plans%2C%20now%20I'm%20in%20charge%20of%20my%20own%20destiny.%20And%20I'm%20glad%20I%20control%20my%20i