ned%20CCTV%20footage%20from%20Delhi%2C%20Hyderabad%2C%20and%20Amritsar%20airports.%20The%20accused%20told%20the%20cops%20how%20he%20executed%20the%20crime%20for%20a%20year%20in%20one%20of%20the%20most%20highly%20secured%20areas%20in%20the%20country%20-%20airports%20-%20and%20managed%20to%20escape.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeputy%20Commissioner%20of%20Delhi%20Police%2C%20Usha%20Rangrani%2C%20said%20the%20man%20targeted%20passengers%20who%20took%20connecting%20flights.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20woman%20travelling%20from%20Hyderabad%20to%20Delhi%20in%20April%20had%20to%20board%20a%20connecting%20Air%20India%20flight%20to%20the%20US%20from%20the%20IGI%20Airport%20in%20Delhi.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20the%20US%20resident%2C%20Varjinderjit%20Singh%2C%20was%20travelling%20to%20Frankfurt%2C%20Germany%20from%20Amritsar%20and%20had%20a%20connecting%20flight%20from%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20senior%20cop%20said%20he%20chose%20the%20elderly%20and%20women%20passengers%20as%20his%20targets%20and%20used%20to%20observe%20their%20behaviour%20at%20the%20airport.%20He%20would%20follow%20them%20or%20slyly%20read%20the%20information%20on%20the%20baggage%20declaration%20slip%20to%20get%20more%20details%20about%20the%20valuables%20inside%20the%20bag.%20The%20police%20said%20they%20saw%20the%20man%20interact%20mostly%20at%20the%20boarding%20gate%2C%20and%20before%20that%2C%20he%20would%20observe%20the%20behaviour%20of%20his%20targets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20police%20said%20the%20accused%20used%20to%20request%20the%20airline%20to%20change%20his%20seat%20so%20that%20he%20could%20be%20next%20to%20the%20passenger.%20Sometimes%2C%20it%20was%20a%20coincidence%2C%20but%20he%20mostly%20would%20give%20a%20reason%20to%20get%20his%20seat%20changed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20cops%20added%20that%20he%20would%20often%20sit%20near%20the%20passenger%20he%20would%20steal%20from%20and%20pretend%20to%20adjust%20the%20bags%20in%20the%20overhead%20section%20and%20steal%20jewellery%20and%20other%20valuables%20while%20other%20passengers%20were%20boarding%20the%20aircraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20phone%20number%20of%20the%20accused%20was%20obtained%20from%20the%20airlines%3B%20however%2C%20he%20entered%20a%20fake%20number%20at%20the%20time%20of%20booking%20to%20defraud%20them%2C%20and%20the%20phone%20number%20was%20registered%20in%20someone%20else's%20name%2C%20making%20sure%20he%20did%20not%20leave%20any%20evidence%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'A%20Guest%20House%20Owner'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERajesh%20owns%20'Ricky%20Deluxe'%2C%20a%20guest%20house%20in%20Delhi%20Paharganj%2C%20close%20to%20the%20New%20Delhi%20Railway%20Station.%20The%20man%20lived%20on%20the%20third%20floor%20of%20the%20guest%20house%2C%20and%20the%20other%20floors%20were%20for%20the%20customers.%20The%20police%20said%20he%20had%20a%20money%20exchange%20business%20and%2C%20also%20owned%20a%20mobile%20repair%20shop%20in%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20stole%20valuables%20from%20bags%20of%20mostly%20female%20passengers%20in%20several%20operating%20from%20airports%20like%20Delhi%2C%20Chennai%2C%20Hyderabad%2C%20Chandigarh%2C%20Bangalore%2C%20Mumbai%2C%20and%20Amritsar.%20A%20large%20quantity%20of%20gold%20and%20silver%20jewellery%20was%20recovered%20from%20his%20house%20in%20Paharganj%3B%20however%2C%20he%20also%20revealed%20that%20on%20several%20occasions%20he%20sold%20the%20stolen%20jewellery%20to%20a%20jeweller%20named%20Sharad%20Jain%20in%20neighbouring%20Karol%20Bagh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20thief%20who%20boarded%20flights%20used%20to%20steal%20in%20trains%20and%20%26quot%3Bgained%20success%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20police%20said.%20After%20getting%20caught%2C%20the%20man%20%26quot%3Bwent%20silent%26quot%3B%20and%20later%20decided%20to%20plan%20thefts%20at%20the%20airports.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715620380000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2Fi0b4jrlg_delhi-thief-_625x300_13_May_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22ht