.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20incredible%20talent%20and%20a%20dogged%20pursuit%20of%20her%20goal%2C%20she%20became%20a%20student%20at%20the%20Massachusetts%20Institute%20of%20Technology%20(MIT)%2C%20which%20was%20a%20huge%20deal%20for%20the%20student%20who%20studied%20in%20a%20state%20board%20school%20and%20came%20from%20a%20middle%20class%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20this%20gritty%20woman%20works%20as%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F324699%2Fawais-ahmed-founded-space-startup-pixxel-hyperspectral-satellite-launch-hyperloop-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaerospace%20engineer%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20National%20Aeronautics%20and%20Space%20Administration%20(NASA).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20her%20journey%20was%20not%20an%20easy%20one.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENavigating%20through%20the%20various%20hurdles%20of%20having%20an%20education%20abroad%20to%20setting%20foot%20at%20NASA%20as%20a%20full-time%20employee%20took%20her%20almost%2015%20years.%20But%20this%2035-year-old%20is%20making%20it%20easy%20for%20others%20by%20sharing%20her%20experiences%20on%20social%20media%2C%20and%20mentoring%20them.%20Here%E2%80%99s%20her%20story.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EIn%20pursuit%20of%20the%20universe%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAkshata%20works%20as%20a%20Principal%20Investigator%20and%20Space%20Systems%20Engineer%20at%20NASA%20Jet%20Propulsion%20Laboratory%20(JPL)%20on%20two%20space%20missions.%20She%20is%20the%20mission%20science%20phase%20lead%20on%20the%20NASA-ISRO%20Synthetic%20Aperture%20Radar%20mission%20(NISAR)%20and%20robotics%20systems%20engineer%20on%20the%20MARS%202020%20Perseverance%20rover%2C%20operating%20the%20rover%20on%20MARS.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20lifelong%20tryst%20with%20space%20took%20roots%20at%20an%20airshow%20in%20Bengaluru%20in%202003.%20It%20was%20the%20Aero%20India%20show%20at%20the%20Yelahanka%20air%20force%20base%20that%20perhaps%20started%20it%20all.%20The%20aerobatic%20manoeuvres%20of%20the%20Sukhoi%20Su-30%20pilots%20left%20the%20youngster%20captivated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-embed%20wp-block-embed-youtube%20wp-embed-aspect-16-9%20wp-has-aspect-ratio%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-embed__wrapper%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FFwPOzvr0oxQ%3Ffeature%3Doembed%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22C0159%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22281%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20was%20always%20interested%20in%20science%20and%20maths%20and%20wanted%20to%20know%20more%20about%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F319013%2Fiit-madras-graduates-startup-agnikul-cosmos-manufactures-3d-printed-rockets-video%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eorigins%20of%20our%20universe%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20wanted%20to%20know%20more%20about%20where%20we%20come%20from%2C%20and%20what%20is%20out%20there%20in%20the%20sky.%20I%20also%20wanted%20to%20travel%20around%20and%20explore%20but%20we%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20the%20resources%20for%20that%2C%E2%80%9D%20Akshata%20tells%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDetermined%2C%20she%20fueled%20her%20curiosity%20with%20whatever%20source%20she%20had%20access%20to%2C%20like%20visiting%20the%20local%20factories%20in%20her%20native%20Karnataka%20village%20or%20visiting%20the%20planetariums.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECalling%20herself%20an%20%E2%80%98explorer%E2%80%99%2C%20Akshata%20would%20find%20joy%20in%20understanding%20the%20hows%20and%20whys%20of%20everything%20she%20laid%20eyes%20upon.%20This%20sense%20of%20reasoning%20helped%20her%20when%20she%20pursued%20engineering%20later.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20major%20turning%20point%20in%20her%20life%20was%20reading%20about%20the%20Hubble%20Space%20telescope%20which%20ignited%20her%20passion%20for%20aerospace.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20early%202000s%2C%20watching%20astronauts%20perform%20spacewalks%20while%20servicing%20the%20Hubble%20telescope%20was%20a%20huge%20inspiration.%20It%20made%20me%20dream%20of%20looking%20at%20Earth%20from%20the%20vast%20reaches%20of%20space%20and%20experiencing%20what%20they%20experienced%2C%E2%80%9D%20shares%20the%20rocket%20scientist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ECarving%20her%20own%20path%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20wanted%20to%20become%20an%20astronaut%20and%20that%20was%20a%20clear%20goal%20in%20my%20mind%2C%E2%80%9D%20recalls%20Akshata.%20In%20the%2090s%2C%20she%20knew%20of%20Rakesh%20Sharma%2C%20Kalpana%20Chawla%20and%20Sunita%20Williams.%20While%20Sharma%20was%20in%20the%20Indian%20air%20force%2C%20the%20other%20two%20were%20US%20citizens.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%202482px)%20100vw%2C%202482px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F05%2F1715219850.743726-min-1715319952.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%222482%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Akshata%20works%20as%20a%20Principal%20Investigator%20and%20Space%20Systems%20Engineer%20at%20NASA%20Jet%20Propulsion%20Laboratory%20(JPL)%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F05%2F1715219850.743726-min-1715319952.jpg%202482w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F05%2F1715219850.743726-min-1715319952-300x204.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F05%2F1715219850.743726-min-1715319952-500x339.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F05%2F1715219850.743726-min-1715319952-768x521.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F05%2F1715219850.743726-min-1715319952-1536x1043.jpg%201536w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F05%2F1715219850.743726-min-1715319952-2048x1390.jpg%202048w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F05%2F1715219850.743726-min-1715319952-150x102.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-349621%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221685%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EAkshata%20works%20as%20a%20Principal%20Investigator%20and%20Space%20Systems%20Engineer%20at%20NASA%20Jet%20Propulsion%20Laboratory%20(JPL)%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAt%20the%20time%2C%20India%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20a%20human%20space%20programme.%20You%20either%20became%20a%20cosmonaut%20with%20Russia%20or%20you%20became%20an%20astronaut%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F295003%2Futtarakhand-scientist-amit-pandey-in-nasa-artemis-moon-rocket-mission%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20space%20programme.%3C%2Fa%3E%20There%20were%20no%20Indians%20who%20weren%E2%80%99t%20US%20citizens%20in%20the%20programme%20then%2C%E2%80%9D%20adds%20Akshata.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20soon%20discovered%20that%20a%20large%20percentage%20of%20astronauts%20had%20actually%20studied%20at%20MIT.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%9CSince%20then%2C%20I%20knew%20that%20I%20had%20to%20study%20at%20MIT%20as%20I%20felt%20that%20it%20would%20provide%20me%20with%20a%20good%20chance%20to%20go%20to%20space.%20MIT%20has%20actually%20sent%2044%20astronauts%20to%20space%20and%20most%20of%20them%20pursued%20their%20PhDs%20here%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20gave%20the%20young%20schoolgirl%20a%20clear%20path%20to%20focus%20on.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20then%20became%20the%20only%20female%20student%20in%20her%20mechanical%20engineering%20stream%20at%20RV%20College%20of%20Engineering%20in%20Bengaluru%2C%20graduating%20in%202010.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20this%2C%20she%20got%20a%20full%20ride%20to%20the%20University%20of%20Illinois%20in%20Urbana-Champaign%20to%20pursue%20a%20masters%20in%20aerospace%20engineering.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20real%20challenge%20before%20Akshata%20presented%20itself%20in%20the%20form%20of%20getting%20an%20aerospace%20job%20in%20the%20US%20without%20a%20citizenship%20or%20a%20green%20card.%20To%20be%20accepted%20as%20a%20doctoral%20candidate%20at%20MIT%2C%20she%20would%20need%20some%20work%20experience%2C%20she%20learned.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20came%20here%20alone%20and%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20any%20support.%20I%20kept%20doing%20research%20projects%20and%20publishing%20papers%20to%20add%20to%20my%20credentials%20to%20show%20that%20I%20can%20create%20an%20impact.%20Every%20opportunity%20I%20got%20was%20never%20luck%20or%20coincidence%2C%20it%20was%20through%20hard%20work%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20engineer%20shares.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20pursuing%20her%20masters%2C%20she%20started%20writing%20to%20professors%20at%20MIT%20that%20she%20wanted%20to%20work%20with%20them%20for%20her%20PhD.%20It%20was%20only%20on%20her%20third%20attempt%20that%20she%20was%20selected.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20honed%20my%20skills%20and%20worked%20outside%20my%20curriculum%20but%20was%20still%20waitlisted%20as%20not%20all%20space%20projects%20can%20take%20foreign%20nationals%20since%20they%20are%20funded%20by%20the%20US%20government%20and%20have%20restrictions.%20But%20when%20I%20was%20waitlisted%20the%20second%20time%2C%20I%20wrote%20to%20all%20the%20professors%20at%20MIT%20asking%20for%20a%20chance%20to%20work%20with%20them%20for%20a%20year.%20Finally%2C%20I%20heard%20back%20from%20professor%20Sara%20Seager%20that%20there%20was%20a%20project%20I%20could%20work%20on%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProfessor%20Seager%20is%20an%20astrophysicist%20and%20planetary%20scientist%20at%20MIT%20who%20focuses%20on%20exoplanet%20research%2C%20which%20is%20the%20discovery%20of%20new%20planets.%20She%20offered%20her%20a%20temporary%20research%20associate%20position%20for%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20that%20time%2C%20Akshata%20had%20two%20options%20%E2%80%94%20take%20a%20well-paying%20job%20at%20the%20likes%20of%20Google%20or%20Amazon%20without%20worrying%20about%20her%20visa%20or%20career%2C%20or%20take%20a%20risk%20and%20work%20on%20a%20new%20research%20project%20which%20was%20incredibly%20exciting.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20no-brainer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-instgrm-version%3D%5C%2214%5C%22%20data-instgrm-permalink%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FC6Y47dFR7g5%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26amp%3Butm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FC6Y47dFR7g5%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3EView%20this%20post%20on%20Instagram%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FC6Y47dFR7g5%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20post%20shared%20by%20Dr.%20Akshata%20Krishnamurthy%20%7C%20NASA%20Rocket%20Scientist%20(%40astro.akshata)%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20working%20for%20a%20year%20on%20exoplanet%20research%2C%20she%20applied%20to%20the%20MIT%20PhD%20programme%20again%2C%20and%20as%20they%20say%2C%20third%20time%E2%80%99s%20the%20charm.%20Under%20Professor%20Seager%2C%20and%20in%20a%20fully-funded%20programme%2C%20she%20finally%20got%20her%20PhD%20in%202020.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMy%20doctorate%20is%20in%20aeronautics%20and%20astronautics%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebut%20I%20worked%20on%20the%20boundary%20of%20science%20and%20engineering%2C%20focusing%20on%20developing%20space%20telescopes%20and%20technologies%20to%20discover%20new%20planets%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20went%20on%20to%20work%20full-time%20at%20the%20NASA%20JPL%2C%20which%2C%20she%20shares%2C%20was%20also%20a%20serendipitous%20occurrence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20worked%20there%20for%20three%20months%20as%20an%20intern%20and%20would%20meet%20with%20managers%20everyday%20asking%20for%20a%20job.%20But%20nobody%20could%20commit%20anything%20to%20me%20without%20a%20green%20card%20as%20it%20involves%20a%20lot%20of%20paperwork%20and%20complexity%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20day%20of%20her%20internship%20arrived%20but%20she%20still%20had%20no%20job%20offers%20or%20interviews.%20Luckily%2C%20she%20had%20a%20presentation%20to%20give%20that%20day.%20A%20hiring%20manager%20in%20the%20audience%20was%20impressed%20with%20Akshata%E2%80%99s%20presentation%20and%20decided%20to%20give%20her%20a%20job.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20then%2C%20till%20the%20paperwork%20came%20through%2C%20the%20scientist%20recalls%20that%20she%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20breathe%20easy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20she%20entered%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F323066%2Fchandrayaan-3-the-history-of-how-india-began-one-of-its-most-significant-space-journeys%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENASA%20JPL%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20an%20employee%20in%20February%202020%2C%20that%20was%20one%20of%20the%20happiest%20days%20of%20her%20life.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Akshata%E2%80%99s%20story%20is%20surely%20inspirational%2C%20we%20ask%2C%20what%20kept%20her%20going%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20was%20adamant%20about%20getting%20into%20NASA%20and%20doing%20whatever%20it%20took%20to%20reach%20that%20goal.%20There%20was%20no%20plan%20B.%20I%20decided%20to%20bet%20on%20myself.%20Failure%20was%20not%20an%20option%2C%20but%20even%20so%2C%20everytime%20I%20failed%2C%20I%20took%20the%20learnings%20from%20it%2C%20and%20did%20something%20different%20to%20proceed%20further%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERealising%20that%20thousands%20of%20students%20in%20India%20need%20appropriate%20guidance%2C%20she%20started%20channels%20on%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fastro.akshata%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInstagram%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2F%40astro.akshata%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EYouTube%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHere%20are%20her%205%20tips%20to%20pursue%20a%20career%20in%20space%3A%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-embed%20wp-block-embed-youtube%20wp-embed-aspect-16-9%20wp-has-aspect-ratio%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-embed__wrapper%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20data-origheight%3D%5C%22270%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%20data-epautoplay%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20data-facadesrc%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FOk5K8w67Q8U%3Fenablejsapi%3D1%26amp%3Bautoplay%3D0%26amp%3Bcc_load_policy%3D0%26amp%3Bcc_lang_pref%3D%26amp%3Biv_load_policy%3D3%26amp%3Bloop%3D0%26amp%3Bmodestbranding%3D0%26amp%3Brel%3D0%26amp%3Bfs%3D1%26amp%3Bplaysinline%3D1%26amp%3Bautohide%3D2%26amp%3Btheme%3Ddark%26amp%3Bcolor%3Dred%26amp%3Bcontrols%3D1%26amp%3B%5C%22%20data-origwidth%3D%5C%2248